tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild anemia (low hemoglobin) with otherwise normal red cell indices, suggesting a non-specific or early-stage anemia. Platelet count is slightly elevated, which may be reactive but is not markedly abnormal. Leukocyte count and other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
